  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3346" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>Azpeitia, 31 August, 1893.</dateline>
        <opener>Dear D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>. Schuchardt, </opener>
        <p>I feel it useless to write a long chapter on my relations with <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1054">Arzac</persName> and <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2983">Webster</persName>. I have throughout sought their friendship. My conscience is tranquil. It is on their side <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">entirely</hi> that the quarrel has been made. I left <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.119">San Sebastian</placeName> on Monday morning after hearing the knocker-thumps on the door of my lodging house and the deadly shots of the troops round the Hôtel de Londres which caused my landlady to say “pues el pueblo se ha levantado contra Sagasta!”. All this stupid wounding and slaughter because the bandmaster Guimon, because of Sagastas presence in the town, refused to play <hi
            rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">Gernikako arbola</hi>. Do they not know that this heavenly air calms the Basque, while the omision of it riles him more than anything? Since then I have been enriching my library &amp; my supplement to <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2939">Vinson</persName> very considerably at Tolosa, at Oñate, here in Azpeitia. Today the Jesuits let me see Aizpitartes manuscript Dictionary of 40,000 words, dated 1785. I have sent a description to <ref target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.4157">
            <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">the Academy</hi>

          </ref>. Tomorrow I go by Elgoibar to Durango, and next day to Bilbao. But address Salamanca where I shall pass the 10<hi
            rendition="#sup">th</hi>. I went to Aranzazu with José Ucelaï the Oñate madman. He says they say <foreign
            xml:lang="eu">niri diritzait Pedro</foreign> = <foreign
            xml:lang="es">yo me llamo Pedro</foreign>. &amp; <foreign
            xml:lang="eu">zelan medikuari diritzaio</foreign> – <foreign xml:lang="es">come [sic] se llama el medico</foreign>?</p>
        <closer>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>. </signed>
        </closer>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
      </div>
    </body>
